;;; tools/search/laws.shard — S5: the LAWS ORACLE (docs/SEARCH.md S5,
;;; slice 4). Requirements as the search oracle: the ∀-laws of a real
;;; interface (std/list's OWN rev_nil / rev_cons), parsed through the
;;; kernel's single goal seam (parse_goal_r + file_rctx — the
;;; tools/prove precedent), the subject fn remapped to the candidate,
;;; and the two goal sides compared under the S4a machine (sym.shard).
;;;
;;; Verdicts per candidate are three-valued and compose over the law
;;; set: any Refuted law refutes (a separable counterexample class —
;;; one symbolic case kills what ground testing kills one value at a
;;; time); all laws Proven proves; anything else is Undecided (sound
;;; incompleteness, counted honestly).
;;;
;;; G3 — CROSS-ENGINE AGREEMENT (the slice gate): over the catalog's
;;; cn_e-clean candidates at a rung, law-Proven ⊆ battery rev-passers
;;; and no rev-passer is law-Refuted — the symbolic and ground
;;; partitions must be consistent wherever both run. Violations are
;;; loud FAILures, not statistics.
;;;
;;; SELF-PIN: the oracle run with the subject fn UNREMAPPED — std/list's
;;; own rev (and len) must symbolically PROVE their own requirements
;;; through reduction + congruence alone. The interface's implementation
;;; is the first candidate the oracle ever judges.
;;;
;;; NOTE this file rides kernel/driver (goal parsing/resolution), whose
;;; closure carries the known pre-existing kernel/types tc_infer measure
;;; gap — so like tools/prove it is exercised by its pinned RUN output,
;;; not as a corpus check target.
;;;
;;; RUN IT: bin/shard_eval run tools/search/laws.shard          (self + g3 1 + g3 2)
;;;         bin/shard_eval run tools/search/laws.shard self     (self-pin only)
;;;         bin/shard_eval run tools/search/laws.shard g3 N     (one rung)

